items.question: What is Invisalign and how does it work?
items.answer: Invisalign uses a series of clear aligners to gently shift your teeth into place. They are nearly invisible and removable for comfort and convenience.

items.question: Am I a candidate for Invisalign?
items.answer: Most teens and adults with mild to moderate misalignment qualify. A consultation with our specialists will confirm your eligibility.

items.question: How long does Invisalign treatment take?
items.answer: Treatment time varies, but many patients see results in 6 to 18 months depending on their case complexity.

items.question: How much does a consultation cost?
items.answer: Initial consultations are often complimentary or have a minimal fee. Contact us to learn about current offers and coverage.

items.question: Is Invisalign treatment covered by insurance?
items.answer: Some dental plans cover Invisalign like braces. We can help you check your benefits and provide financing options.
